Lecture 6 microservices
Alright, let’s talk microservices — this is one of those terms that sounds fancy but the core idea is actually pretty intuitive once you picture it.
🌱 Big picture first (intuition)
Imagine you’re building Amazon.
Two ways:
🧱 Monolith (old style)
Everything in ONE giant app:
login
payment
search
recommendation
order system
All in one codebase, one deployment.
👉 Like one giant bowl of spaghetti
Change one noodle → everything shakes 😅
🧩 Microservices (modern style)
Split system into many small services:
auth service
payment service
product service
search service
recommendation service
Each runs independently and talks through APIs.
👉 Like LEGO blocks
Swap one piece → others don’t break.


One giant app.

If only search gets heavy traffic…

👉 you still must scale the entire system

So you add:

5 → 10 → 20 full copies of EVERYTHING


Even parts nobody uses (like admin panel).

💸 wasteful + expensive

🧩 Microservices scaling

Now split into:

search service

payment service

user service

recommendation service

If search is hot:

👉 scale ONLY search

search: 20 instances
payment: 2 instances
user: 3 instances


🔥 Much cheaper + faster + smarter

